:''For the Singapore system, see [[Electronic Road Pricing (Singapore)]].''

'''Electronic road pricing''' is the technology and mechanism to toll drivers [[electronic toll collection|by electronic means]] in an area within which [[road pricing]] is imposed. It was first put into trial in Hong Kong in the early 1980s, but its implementation was aborted. Current systems include Singapore, [[Singapore]]; London, England, United Kingdom; and Stockholm, Sweden.




